  "texts": [
    "The production processes for biomaterials, which include fermentation, extraction, and processing, require energy input (Mishra et al. 2023).",
    "Although the energy consumption of biomaterials is usually lower compared to the production process of traditional materials, there is still a particular energy consumption and possible carbon emissions.",
    "Therefore, to reduce the environmental impact of biomaterial production, more renewable and clean energy sources should be sought to meet production needs.",
    "However, the production of biological materials can also enable the recycling of materials and positively contribute to the environment.",
    "For example, the production process of building materials based on hemp guarantees that 29% of the fibers and 14% of the shives are recycled (Dutreix et al. 2017)."
  ],
